# Codebase context (express-mongoose)

## What this repo is
- Single Node.js app (not a monorepo) built with **Express 4** + **Mongoose**.
- Server-side rendered UI using **EJS** templates.
- Implements a simple shop flow: products, product detail, cart, orders, and admin product CRUD.
- Authentication is session-based (login/signup/logout).

## Key runtime dependencies
- express, body-parser
- mongoose
- express-session + connect-mongodb-session
- csurf (CSRF protection)
- connect-flash (flash messages)
- bcryptjs (password hashing)

## App entrypoint
- `app.js`
  - Creates the Express app
  - Configures sessions (MongoDB-backed) and CSRF
  - Loads the logged-in user from the session and sets `req.user`
  - Registers routes (`/admin`, shop, auth)
  - 404 handler
  - Connects to MongoDB via `process.env.MONGODB_URI`
  - Starts server on port `3000`

## Main folders and responsibilities
- `routes/`
  - `routes/admin.js` ‚Äî admin product routes (protected by `middleware/is-auth.js`)
  - `routes/shop.js` ‚Äî shop pages + cart + orders (cart/orders protected)
  - `routes/auth.js` ‚Äî login/signup/logout routes
- `controllers/`
  - `controllers/admin.js` ‚Äî admin product CRUD handlers
  - `controllers/shop.js` ‚Äî product list/detail + cart + order handlers
  - `controllers/auth.js` ‚Äî login/signup/logout handlers
  - `controllers/error.js` ‚Äî 404 handler
- `models/`
  - `models/product.js` ‚Äî Product schema (includes `userId` ref)
  - `models/user.js` ‚Äî User schema + cart methods (`addToCart`, `removeFromCart`, `clearCart`)
  - `models/order.js` ‚Äî Order schema (stores product snapshots + user reference)
- `middleware/`
  - `middleware/is-auth.js` ‚Äî redirects to `/login` when not authenticated
- `views/` ‚Äî EJS templates
- `public/` ‚Äî static assets

## Authentication & session flow
- Login sets:
  - `req.session.isLoggedIn = true`
  - `req.session.user = user`
- Per-request middleware in `app.js`:
  - If `req.session.user` exists, loads the user from MongoDB and assigns to `req.user`
- Authorization:
  - `middleware/is-auth.js` checks `req.session.isLoggedIn`

## Database notes
- Mongo connection uses `process.env.MONGODB_URI`.
- Session store uses the same MongoDB URI and stores sessions in the `sessions` collection.

## Common patterns in this codebase
- Controllers use promise chains (`.then().catch()`) rather than `async/await`.
- Rendering uses `res.render(view, { ... })` and templates expect:
  - `isAuthenticated` (frequently passed explicitly)
  - `csrfToken` available via `res.locals.csrfToken` (set in `app.js`)